## Implementation
NuGet has a flat container API:
```bash
curl 'https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/{package}/index.json'
```
Returns JSON with `versions` array. Need to get last stable (non-prerelease) version.

## Cannot use simple JsonApiSource
Versions are in array, need to filter prereleases and get latest. Options:
1. Custom NuGetSource that parses array
2. Extend JsonApiSource to handle arrays

## Suggested implementation:
```rust
pub struct NuGetSource;

impl Source for NuGetSource {
    fn name(&self) -> &'static str { "nuget" }
    fn ecosystem(&self) -> Ecosystem { Ecosystem::Dotnet }

    fn get_version(&self, package: &str) -> Option<String> {
        let url = format!("https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/{}/index.json", package.to_lowercase());
        let output = Command::new("curl").args(["-sf", &url]).output().ok()?;
        if !output.status.success() { return None; }

        // Parse versions array, filter prereleases, get last
        let json = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
        json.split('"')
            .filter(|v| v.chars().next().map(|c| c.is_ascii_digit()).unwrap_or(false))
            .filter(|v| !v.contains('-'))  // Skip prereleases
            .last()
            .map(|v| v.to_string())
    }
}
```

