## Implementation
Swift packages are Git repos. Can use GitHub API for GitHub-hosted packages:
```bash
curl 'https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo}/tags'
```
Returns array of tags, first one is latest.

## Challenges:
1. Package URLs are full git URLs (e.g., `https://github.com/apple/swift-argument-parser`)
2. Need to parse owner/repo from URL
3. Rate limiting on GitHub API (60 req/hr unauthenticated)
4. Non-GitHub packages won't work

## Suggested implementation:
```rust
pub struct SwiftSource;

impl Source for SwiftSource {
    fn name(&self) -> &'static str { "swift" }
    fn ecosystem(&self) -> Ecosystem { Ecosystem::Swift }

    fn get_version(&self, package: &str) -> Option<String> {
        // Extract owner/repo from github.com URL or owner/repo format
        let (owner, repo) = parse_github_repo(package)?;
        let url = format!("https://api.github.com/repos/{}/{}/tags", owner, repo);
        let output = Command::new("curl").args(["-sf", &url]).output().ok()?;
        if !output.status.success() { return None; }

        // Get first tag name (latest)
        let json = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
        extract_json_path(&json, "0.name")
            .map(|v| v.strip_prefix('v').unwrap_or(&v).to_string())
    }
}

fn parse_github_repo(package: &str) -> Option<(&str, &str)> {
    let package = package.trim_start_matches("https://")
        .trim_start_matches("github.com/")
        .trim_end_matches(".git");
    let mut parts = package.split('/');
    Some((parts.next()?, parts.next()?))
}
```

